Usage: seedbank [-e]|[-M macaddress] [-r recipe] [-o overlay] [-m manifest] [-s seed] [-c override] <fqdn> <release>|-l|-p

seedbank - Debian/Ubuntu netboot installations the way it's meant to be
(c) 2009-2012 Jasper Poppe <jpoppe@ebay.com>

Options:
  --version             show program's version number and exit
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -M MACADDRESS, --macaddress=MACADDRESS
                        use mac address as pxe filename
  -e, --externalhost    get the node information from an external source
  -l, --list            list available releases, (disk) recipes and manifests
  -r RECIPES, --recipe=RECIPES
                        choose (disk) recipe(s)
  -m MANIFESTS, --manifest=MANIFESTS
                        choose Puppet manifest(s) to apply after the
                        installation
  -o OVERLAY, --overlay=OVERLAY
                        choose an overlay from which files/templates should be
                        copied
  -u UDEBS, --udeb=UDEBS
                        choose custom udebs to use in the installer
  -s SEED, --seed=SEED  override default seed file (default: distribution
                        name)
  -a SEED_ADDITIONAL, --seed-additional=SEED_ADDITIONAL
                        append additional seed files to the default seed file
  -c CUSTOM, --custom=CUSTOM
                        override setting(s) from settings.py
                        (dict:key:'new_value')
  -p, --listpxefiles    list all pxe host configs
  -v PXEVARIABLES, --variables=PXEVARIABLES
                        specify additional pxe variables, (name value)
